column5: Cool Pic, for sure!!  My house is just a bit south  Rick
Cool, thanks for posting that Joey...My old house was just outside of that picture of Waubaushene...
My sister's husband is a pilot and took this shot the other day.  Thought some of you might think it was interesting!!
thats awesome joey !!!! great view....looks like he was a few miles east of the lake facing west ?? cool....
real cool
Very cool pic ! Its amazing how 15000 ft can make simcoe look like a flyin lake at 1000 ft.
I SEE TERRY,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,   Great shot.
Love those God shots. Hell, I can even see Brechin from there. And Canal Lake....
How about Waubushene from 2,000 feet?   Pre-fishing .... from a Cessna.
Very cool!
Nice shot, seems like there's no one living around the lake.
No backgrounds.
Hmmm, I believe that's georgian bay actually. Cool shot Joey!
nope, GB is in the background beyond Simcoe.
Ya, I love the shot, I'll tell my Bro in law Hamish that you all liked it.  I'll tell him to take some more
Would be super cool if he flew over Lakair and the West Arm ! You should try and snag a ride on the next flight Joey
Hahahaha, he flies commercial, so I'd have to pay for a ticket somewhere.
yeah, co-pilot would probably wonder why you're in his/her seat lol
cool
That's what I'm saying, I don't see canal...
Canal would be in the foreground, Christopher.....seek and ye shall find.
Man.. I can see my house from there!!  BTW.. the Lakair shots have been done by someone else in the past!!
yeah, Canal *should* be on the very edge at right but I can't see it
Lake Simcoe!?!?!?  Never heard of it.  Looks like a big lake though, any fish in it?  Thanks for posting.  I'll have to look it up.
don't bother, no gar in the lake  and too big in the winter for a bravo with a primer problem
